<h2>%%ReferenceStyle%%Book, seven or more authors</h2>
<hr>
<br>
<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">
	Author, Initial(s), Author, Initial(s), Author, Initial(s), Author, Initial(s), Author, 
	Initial(s), Author, Initial(s) et al. Year of publication, <em>Title of book</em>, Publisher, 
	Place of publication.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Examples</strong>
<br>
<br>
If a book has more than six authors, give the first six authors&#8217; names and abbreviate the 
remaining authors to et al. (meaning: &#34;and others&#34;).
<br>
<blockquote class="ref">
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Davis</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Initial(s)">M</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Charles</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Initial(s)">L</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Curry</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Initial(s)">MJ</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Shanti</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Initial(s)">P</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Prasad</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Initial(s)">S</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Hewings</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Initial(s)">A</span> et al.
	<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2003</span>,
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of book">Challenging spatial norms</span></em>,
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Routledge</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Place of publication">London</span>.
</blockquote>
<br>
For a numbered edition, place the abbreviation after the book title. This part should not be italicised. 
Use rev. edn, for revised editions.
<br>
